705220f-b.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Ocean Avenue
705220f-b.text:
King's Highway, at the S.W. corner of Ocean Ave., showing the Wynant Bennett house which was erected by him in 1825 and occupied by a Bennett until its demolition in 1928. In 1872 the house was turned to face west so as not to interfere with the opening of Ocean Ave.
1922.
Eugene L Armbruster Collection.
The same, showing the well and barns.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
The same, showing only the barn.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

705227f-b.title: Brooklyn: Kings Highway - Avenue P
705227f-b.text:
(1)
King's Highway, east from King's Highway and Ave. P., showing at left the B.G. Hitching's house and beyond it in the distance tho "Sanate" or "The Club House", both of which were demolished in 1928.
August 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, showing the N.W. corner of East 26th Street and King's Pighway, the home of Pat Whallen in 1873. This house still stands, and id No. 2519 King's Highway. In the background is the steel structure which, when completed, will be Congress Arms a 6-story apartment house.
August 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
